{
  "work_slug": "alices-adventures-in-wonderland-by-lewis-carroll-5",
  "work_title": "Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (version 4)",
  "work_author": "Lewis Carroll",
  "audio_file": "audio-09",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/alices_adventures_1005_librivox/wonderland_09_carroll.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "09 - The Mock Turtle's Story",
  "reader_name": "Eric Leach",
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.768,
  "page_num": 3,
  "page_total": 4,
  "page_start_sec": 497.76,
  "page_end_sec": 743.74,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 497.76,
      "end": 498.56,
      "text": "This here young lady,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 498.7,
      "end": 499.54,
      "text": "said the Gryphon,"
    },
    {
      "start": 499.64,
      "end": 500.88,
      "text": "she wants to know your history,"
    },
    {
      "start": 501.04,
      "end": 501.28,
      "text": "she do."
    },
    {
      "start": 503.072,
      "end": 503.94,
      "text": "I'll tell it her,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 504.26,
      "end": 506.64,
      "text": "said the Mock Turtle in a deep, hollow tone:"
    },
    {
      "start": 506.9,
      "end": 507.94,
      "text": "sit down,"
    },
    {
      "start": 508.08,
      "end": 508.86,
      "text": "both of you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 508.96,
      "end": 511.5,
      "text": "and don't speak a word till I've finished."
    },
    {
      "start": 512.78,
      "end": 513.6,
      "text": "So they sat down,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 513.74,
      "end": 515.4,
      "text": "and nobody spoke for some minutes."
    },
    {
      "start": 516.096,
      "end": 516.88,
      "text": "Alice thought to herself,"
    },
    {
      "start": 517.32,
      "end": 519.58,
      "text": "I don't see how he can _ever_ finish, if he doesn't begin."
    },
    {
      "start": 520.12,
      "end": 521.34,
      "text": "But she waited patiently."
    },
    {
      "start": 521.88,
      "end": 523.24,
      "text": "Once,"
    },
    {
      "start": 523.34,
      "end": 525.92,
      "text": "said the Mock Turtle at last, with a deep sigh,"
    },
    {
      "start": 526.48,
      "end": 528.28,
      "text": "I was a real Turtle."
    },
    {
      "start": 529.62,
      "end": 531.86,
      "text": "These words were followed by a very long silence,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 532.14,
      "end": 533.74,
      "text": "broken only by an occasional"
    },
    {
      "start": 533.9,
      "end": 534.82,
      "text": "exclamation of"
    },
    {
      "start": 534.84,
      "end": 535.34,
      "text": "Hjckrrh!"
    },
    {
      "start": 536.12,
      "end": 539.28,
      "text": "from the Gryphon, and the constant heavy sobbing of the Mock Turtle."
    },
    {
      "start": 540.736,
      "end": 542.72,
      "text": "Alice was very nearly getting up and saying,"
    },
    {
      "start": 542.86,
      "end": 543.78,
      "text": "Thank you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 543.86,
      "end": 544.06,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 544.1,
      "end": 545.08,
      "text": "for your interesting story,"
    },
    {
      "start": 545.6,
      "end": 548.46,
      "text": "but she could not help thinking there _must_ be more to come,"
    },
    {
      "start": 548.66,
      "end": 550.36,
      "text": "so she sat still and said nothing."
    },
    {
      "start": 552.064,
      "end": 553.26,
      "text": "When we were little,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 554.0,
      "end": 555.6,
      "text": "the Mock Turtle went on at last,"
    },
    {
      "start": 555.6,
      "end": 556.26,
      "text": "more calmly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 556.46,
      "end": 558.36,
      "text": "though still sobbing a little now and then,"
    },
    {
      "start": 558.9,
      "end": 560.88,
      "text": "we went to school in the sea."
    },
    {
      "start": 561.58,
      "end": 563.92,
      "text": "The master was an old Turtle--"
    },
    {
      "start": 564.42,
      "end": 566.28,
      "text": "we used to call him Tortoise----"
    },
    {
      "start": 567.76,
      "end": 569.86,
      "text": "Why did you call him Tortoise, if he wasn't one?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 570.04,
      "end": 571.06,
      "text": "Alice asked."
    },
    {
      "start": 571.8,
      "end": 575.04,
      "text": "We called him Tortoise because he taught us,"
    },
    {
      "start": 576.6,
      "end": 577.91,
      "text": "said the Mock Turtle angrily:"
    },
    {
      "start": 578.8,
      "end": 579.48,
      "text": "really,"
    },
    {
      "start": 579.76,
      "end": 581.28,
      "text": "you are very dull!"
    },
    {
      "start": 582.54,
      "end": 584.02,
      "text": "You ought to be ashamed of yourself"
    },
    {
      "start": 584.02,
      "end": 585.54,
      "text": "for asking such a simple question,"
    },
    {
      "start": 586.14,
      "end": 586.78,
      "text": "added the Gryphon;"
    },
    {
      "start": 586.86,
      "end": 589.3,
      "text": "and then they both sat silent and looked at poor Alice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 589.52,
      "end": 591.32,
      "text": "who felt ready to sink into the earth."
    },
    {
      "start": 592.28,
      "end": 594.32,
      "text": "At last the Gryphon said to the Mock Turtle,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 594.976,
      "end": 595.3,
      "text": "Drive on,"
    },
    {
      "start": 595.32,
      "end": 595.7,
      "text": "old fellow!"
    },
    {
      "start": 595.86,
      "end": 597.06,
      "text": "Don't be all day about it!"
    },
    {
      "start": 597.72,
      "end": 598.98,
      "text": "and he went on in these words:"
    },
    {
      "start": 599.18,
      "end": 599.328,
      "text": "Yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 601.1,
      "end": 603.32,
      "text": "we went to school in the sea,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 603.66,
      "end": 605.22,
      "text": "though you mayn't believe it----"
    },
    {
      "start": 606.08,
      "end": 607.52,
      "text": "I never said I didn't!",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 607.52,
      "end": 608.26,
      "text": "interrupted Alice."
    },
    {
      "start": 609.04,
      "end": 609.48,
      "text": "You did,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 609.88,
      "end": 610.88,
      "text": "said the Mock Turtle."
    },
    {
      "start": 612.06,
      "end": 612.58,
      "text": "Hold your tongue!",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 612.84,
      "end": 614.98,
      "text": "added the Gryphon, before Alice could speak again."
    },
    {
      "start": 615.52,
      "end": 616.74,
      "text": "The Mock Turtle went on:--"
    },
    {
      "start": 618.3,
      "end": 620.49,
      "text": "We had the best of educations--",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 621.48,
      "end": 621.96,
      "text": "in fact,"
    },
    {
      "start": 621.96,
      "end": 623.98,
      "text": "we went to school every day----"
    },
    {
      "start": 625.408,
      "end": 626.44,
      "text": "_I've_ been to a day-school,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 626.54,
      "end": 626.74,
      "text": "too,"
    },
    {
      "start": 626.94,
      "end": 627.5,
      "text": "said Alice;"
    },
    {
      "start": 627.82,
      "end": 629.38,
      "text": "you needn't be so proud as all that."
    },
    {
      "start": 630.92,
      "end": 631.56,
      "text": "With extras?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 632.19,
      "end": 634.38,
      "text": "asked the Mock Turtle a little anxiously."
    },
    {
      "start": 634.9,
      "end": 635.1,
      "text": "Yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 635.34,
      "end": 635.84,
      "text": "said Alice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 635.98,
      "end": 637.06,
      "text": "we learned French and music."
    },
    {
      "start": 638.04,
      "end": 638.56,
      "text": "And washing?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 639.15,
      "end": 640.26,
      "text": "said the Mock Turtle."
    },
    {
      "start": 641.088,
      "end": 641.62,
      "text": "Certainly not!"
    },
    {
      "start": 641.84,
      "end": 643.1,
      "text": "said Alice indignantly."
    },
    {
      "start": 644.38,
      "end": 644.56,
      "text": "Ah!",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 644.78,
      "end": 647.34,
      "text": "then yours wasn't a really good school,"
    },
    {
      "start": 647.92,
      "end": 650.1,
      "text": "said the Mock Turtle in a tone of relief."
    },
    {
      "start": 650.88,
      "end": 654.53,
      "text": "Now at _ours_ they had at the end of the bill, 'French,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 654.98,
      "end": 655.54,
      "text": "music,"
    },
    {
      "start": 655.8,
      "end": 657.56,
      "text": "_and washing_--extra.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 659.44,
      "end": 661.16,
      "text": "You couldn't have wanted it much,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 661.38,
      "end": 661.88,
      "text": "said Alice;"
    },
    {
      "start": 662.04,
      "end": 663.38,
      "text": "living at the bottom of the sea."
    },
    {
      "start": 664.66,
      "end": 666.6,
      "text": "I couldn't afford to learn it,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 666.7,
      "end": 668.42,
      "text": "said the Mock Turtle with a sigh."
    },
    {
      "start": 668.92,
      "end": 671.26,
      "text": "I only took the regular course."
    },
    {
      "start": 672.72,
      "end": 673.2,
      "text": "What was that?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 673.4,
      "end": 674.3,
      "text": "inquired Alice."
    },
    {
      "start": 675.712,
      "end": 677.14,
      "text": "Reeling and Writhing,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 677.14,
      "end": 677.68,
      "text": "of course,"
    },
    {
      "start": 677.7,
      "end": 678.58,
      "text": "to begin with,"
    },
    {
      "start": 679.0,
      "end": 680.28,
      "text": "the Mock Turtle replied;"
    },
    {
      "start": 680.54,
      "end": 683.96,
      "text": "and then the different branches of Arithmetic--"
    },
    {
      "start": 684.6,
      "end": 685.48,
      "text": "Ambition,"
    },
    {
      "start": 685.98,
      "end": 686.72,
      "text": "Distraction,"
    },
    {
      "start": 687.86,
      "end": 688.52,
      "text": "Uglification,"
    },
    {
      "start": 689.14,
      "end": 690.52,
      "text": "and Derision."
    },
    {
      "start": 691.02,
      "end": 693.06,
      "text": "I never heard of 'Uglification,'"
    },
    {
      "start": 693.6,
      "end": 694.7,
      "text": "Alice ventured to say."
    },
    {
      "start": 694.84,
      "end": 695.48,
      "text": "What is it?"
    },
    {
      "start": 696.48,
      "end": 698.68,
      "text": "The Gryphon lifted up both its paws in surprise.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 699.08,
      "end": 700.88,
      "text": "Never heard of uglifying!"
    },
    {
      "start": 701.16,
      "end": 701.94,
      "text": "it exclaimed."
    },
    {
      "start": 702.3,
      "end": 702.5,
      "text": "You know"
    },
    {
      "start": 702.66,
      "end": 703.66,
      "text": "what to beautify is,"
    },
    {
      "start": 703.74,
      "end": 704.08,
      "text": "I suppose?"
    },
    {
      "start": 704.46,
      "end": 704.56,
      "text": "Yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 705.92,
      "end": 707.04,
      "text": "said Alice doubtfully:"
    },
    {
      "start": 707.18,
      "end": 709.2,
      "text": "it means--to--make--anything--prettier."
    },
    {
      "start": 710.88,
      "end": 711.26,
      "text": "Well, then,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 711.48,
      "end": 712.32,
      "text": "the Gryphon went on,"
    },
    {
      "start": 712.42,
      "end": 714.16,
      "text": "if you don't know what to uglify is,"
    },
    {
      "start": 714.24,
      "end": 714.93,
      "text": "you are a simpleton."
    },
    {
      "start": 716.288,
      "end": 719.38,
      "text": "Alice did not feel encouraged to ask any more questions about it,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 719.72,
      "end": 721.44,
      "text": "so she turned to the Mock Turtle and said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 722.14,
      "end": 723.18,
      "text": "What else had you to learn?"
    },
    {
      "start": 724.36,
      "end": 725.18,
      "text": "Well,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 725.4,
      "end": 726.66,
      "text": "there was Mystery,"
    },
    {
      "start": 727.2,
      "end": 728.42,
      "text": "the Mock Turtle replied,"
    },
    {
      "start": 728.68,
      "end": 730.68,
      "text": "counting off the subjects on his flappers,"
    },
    {
      "start": 730.82,
      "end": 732.42,
      "text": "--Mystery,"
    },
    {
      "start": 732.7,
      "end": 734.42,
      "text": "ancient and modern,"
    },
    {
      "start": 734.58,
      "end": 736.22,
      "text": "with Seaography:"
    },
    {
      "start": 736.22,
      "end": 737.56,
      "text": "then Drawling--"
    },
    {
      "start": 738.12,
      "end": 741.14,
      "text": "the Drawling-master was an old conger-eel,"
    },
    {
      "start": 741.8,
      "end": 743.74,
      "text": "that used to come once a week:"
    }
  ]
}
